GitFlow branching strategy is followed for above task, GitFlow is a structured branching strategy that uses separate branches 
for development, release, and production to enable controlled and stable software delivery.
In this branching startegy 3 different repos are present Application, Deployment, Infrastructure repos (repos are created by DevOps Engineer)
In Application Repo : The Application Repository (app-repo) is where your actual application code and build logic live
app-repo/
 ├── src/
 │    ├── main/
 │    │    ├── java/
 │    │    └── resources/
 │    └── test/
 ├── pom.xml
 ├── Dockerfile
 ├── Jenkinsfile
 ├── application.yml
 ├── sonar-project.properties
 ├── README.md
 └── .gitignore
* Branches Inside Application Repo (GitFlow)
main        → production
develop     → integration
feature/*   → new features
release/*   → release prep
hotfix/*    → production fixes
