What is a Deployment Repository?
👉 The Deployment Repository contains everything needed to deploy your application to different environments (DEV, QA, PP, PROD).
👉 It does NOT contain application source code
👉 It uses the artifact (Docker image) built from the Application Repository
DEPLOYMENT-REPO/
 ├── helm/
 │    └── myapp/
 ├── environments/
 │    ├── dev/
 │    ├── qa/
 │    ├── pp/
 │    └── prod/
 ├── Jenkinsfile
 ├── scripts/
 └── README.md
*********************************************************************************************************************************************
What is an Infrastructure Repository?
👉 The Infrastructure Repository (infra-repo) contains code to create, manage, and version infrastructure using Infrastructure as Code (IaC).
👉 Instead of manually creating servers, networks, and databases, you define everything in code using Terraform.
INFRA-REPO/
 ├── modules/
 │    ├── vpc/
 │    ├── ec2/
 │    ├── rds/
 │    └── eks/
 │
 ├── environments/
 │    ├── dev/
 │    ├── qa/
 │    ├── pp/
 │    └── prod/
 │
 ├── backend/
 │    └── backend.tf
 │
 ├── providers.tf
 ├── variables.tf
 ├── outputs.tf
 └── README.md

👉 “We maintain three separate repositories—application, deployment, and infrastructure—to achieve separation of concerns, 
independent lifecycle management, better security, team ownership, and scalable CI/CD pipelines.”
 
